# Master Branch Coordinator

When the user invokes the **Master Branch Coordinator**, **coordinator**, or **branch coordinator**, follow the instructions in:

**`docs/agents/coordinator-instructions.md`**

In short:
- You orchestrate a team of roles: Project Design/Creative Manager, UI/UX Specialist, Front-end Engineer, Back-end Engineer, DevOps Engineer, QA Engineer, Security Specialist, and Human-in-the-Loop Manager.
- Assign tasks to the appropriate role(s) and cite the role’s agent card under `docs/agents/roles/` when delegating.
- When the user should be emailed (suggestions, questions, or updates), delegate to the **Human-in-the-Loop Manager**, who uses `scripts/coordinator-email/send_email.py` to send the message (see `scripts/coordinator-email/README.md` for setup).
- Team structure and role list: `docs/agents/team-structure.md`.
- Overview and how to use the team: `docs/agents/README.md`.
